										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;re halfway through June already, with loads of blog posts behind us! Here&#8217;s the latest batch:</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-27851" src="https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-200x300.jpg 200w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/griffin-wooldridge-aFMsnhkZoJg-unsplash-scaled.jpg 1707w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<ul>
<li>On <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/issue-050-author-interview-lisa-farrell-and-crowd-demons/"><strong>Tuesday</strong></a>, we explored the Victorian era and all its spookiness in <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/issue/issue-050/">Issue 050</a> story &#8220;<a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/story/crowd-demons/">Crowd Demons</a>&#8221; by Lisa Farrell;</li>
<li>On <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/submissions/"><strong>Wednesday</strong></a>, we opened for submissions for our TREE-themed issue;</li>
<li>On <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/review-the-impossible-resurrection-of-grief-by-octavia-cade/"><strong>Thursday</strong></a>, Joanna Weston reviewed Octavia Cade&#8217;s cli-fi novella <em>The Impossible Resurrection of Grief</em>;</li>
<li>On <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/look-ahead-writers-and-make-a-plan/"><strong>Friday</strong></a>, Ann Langley advised us, the help of the Tarot, to make a writing plan over the next month.</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
