<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-27623" src="https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-300x200.jpg 300w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-768x512.jpg 768w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://lunastationquarterly.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/johnny-kaufman-RhRu1h2NttE-unsplash-2048x1365.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<ul>
<li>On <a href="https://lunastationquarterly.com/the-cards-say-go-for-it/"><strong>Monday</strong></a>, Ann Langley started her new column &#8220;Story Mystic&#8221; in which she pulls five Tarot cards for writers;</li>
